  "notes": "Balinese (Basa Bali) in the Latin orthography (the Balinese script, Aksara Bali, is also in use and is not covered here). Indonesian-style spelling conventions: ⟨c⟩=/tʃ/, ⟨j⟩=/dʒ/, ⟨ny⟩=/ɲ/, ⟨ng⟩=/ŋ/. Six vowels /i e ə a o u/; ⟨e⟩ writes both /e/ and /ə/ and word-final orthographic ⟨-a⟩ is typically realised as [ə]. ⟨f v z q x⟩ occur only in loanwords.",
